shock, might want to peek here: http://www.subgenius.com

It's stupid, but sometimes stupidity is a nice vacation, and somtimes
outrageous nonsense kick-starts the senses.


Sandra

>>I don't describe myself as atheist in real life, but for the team-claiming
>>in this conversation I was one.<<

Yeah team!


>>I wonder if someone could show by an analysis of my books what religion?
>>If so, it might be Anthropologeism or Dabblation. I have lots of Bibles,
>>but more Zen books. I'm not afraid of Beavis and Butthead or Kyle and
>>Cartman. I like humorous surprise. What religion is that?>>

How about The Church of the Subgenious, which shares the sacred teachings of
J.R. "Bob" Dobbs? "Researching the Public's Fear of the Unknown Since 1953!"

And including the TriPrimality:

"Bob"is.
"Bob" becomes.
"Bob" is not.
Nothing is;Nothing becomes;
Nothing is not.

Thus: Nothing is everything.
Therefore: Everything is "Bob."
Abracadabra

~Mary
